Acknowledgement
The National Curriculum Development Centre (NCDC) would like to express its appreciation to all those who worked
tirelessly on the 'O' level (UCE) Curriculum Teaching syllabi
Gratitude goes first to the Ministry of Education and Sport for ensuring that funds were made available to support the
writing of the different subject syllabi.
The various writing activities benefited greatly from our partners in education who provided the professional information
and advise that was put together to come up with content and information for the teacher in the school.
They include Secondary schools, Universities, National Teacher Colleges, Uganda National Examinations Board (UNEB),
Directorate of Education Standards (DES), Technical and Business institutions, Private Organisation, Religious
Organisation and Ministry of Education and Sports officials.
Last but not least we would like to acknowledge all those behind the scenes who formed part of the team that worked hard
to finalise the work on the various syllabi.
Connie Kateeba
DIRECTOR,
National Curriculum Development Centre

Acknowledgement


The National Curriculum Development Centre (NCDC) would like to express its appreciation to all those who worked tirelessly on the 'O' level (UCE) Curriculum Teaching syllabi


Gratitude goes first to the Ministry of Education and Sport for ensuring that funds were made available to support the writing of the different subject syllabi.


The various writing activities benefited greatly from our partners in education who provided the professional information and advise that was put together to come up with content and information for the teacher in the school.


They include Secondary schools, Universities, National Teacher Colleges, Uganda National Examinations Board (UNEB), Directorate of Education Standards (DES), Technical and Business institutions, Private Organisation, Religious Organisation and Ministry of Education and Sports officials.


Last but not least we would like to acknowledge all those behind the scenes who formed part of the team that worked hard to finalise the work on the various syllabi.


Connie Kateeba DIRECTOR, National Curriculum Development Centre
